1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 27=

3
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,040
You're resigning?

4
00:01:48,088 --> 00:01:49,111
Where are you going?

5
00:01:49,955 --> 00:01:50,760
To Dingqi Platform?

6
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,360
So how long have you been

7
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,511
in contact with Mr. Fan?

8
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,080
Just these past two months.

9
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:03,680
He contacted me
through a headhunting agency.

10
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,480
Then, did you give
Mr. Fan or Zhao Lanxin

11
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,480
the company's list of new authors?

12
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,080
I didn't.

13
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:09,511
And the photos of He Han and me.

14
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:10,720
What photos?

15
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:13,640
So you're saying

16
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,080
you never passed

17
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,200
company information to Mr. Fan

18
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,040
or Zhao Lanxin?

19
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,000
That's against company policy.

20
00:02:20,755 --> 00:02:22,444
Why would I do something like that?

21
00:02:25,244 --> 00:02:26,360
So what you're saying is

22
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,840
someone's been leaking
information all along?

23
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:33,960
Ms. Lin,

24
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,920
my job does involve

25
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:37,480
a lot of outside communication.

26
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,360
But I really never did

27
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,280
this kind of thing.

28
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,000
Besides...

29
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:45,680
Besides, I'm resigning soon anyway.

30
00:02:45,844 --> 00:02:47,520
There's no reason for me to lie to you.

31
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,160
Sorry.

32
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,480
Maybe I was wrong.

33
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,280
I hope it wasn't you.

34
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:15,840
Even more so,

35
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,480
I hope it wasn't any of you.

36
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,440
About your resignation,

37
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,080
I hope you won't make it public yet.

38
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,320
We're in a tough spot right now.

39
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,200
Don't affect the others.

40
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:31,320
Don't worry.

41
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,520
I'll sort out all my work and authors

42
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:37,160
before handing everything over to you.

43
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,000
After I leave,

44
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,355
you can tell everyone then.

45
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,560
Sorry, Ms. Lin, I...

46
00:03:52,444 --> 00:03:53,600
I'll get going first.

47
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,640
See you around.

48
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,400
See you around.

49
00:04:05,580 --> 00:04:07,333
(Signing Author Authorization
Cooperation Agreement)

50
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,240
The lawyers have already reviewed
the agreement signed

51
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,577
between Gu Yan and Lin Zhanqiao.

52
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:17,240
Lawyer Bei handled it back then.

53
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,120
The terms are really strict.

54
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,880
But...

55
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,680
where there are terms,

56
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,000
there are loopholes.

57
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,720
As long as Gu Yan insists

58
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:32,280
that Lin Zhanqiao
failed to fulfill her obligations,

59
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,320
you can reduce the compensation a bit.

60
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,520
Compensation still has to be paid.

61
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:43,320
Lin Zhanqiao concealed the fact
that Chenxing was developing

62
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,480
similar authors to compete with Gu Yan.

63
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,120
And when settling
copyright earnings for Gu Yan's works,

64
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:49,560
Chenxing also

65
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,200
made late payments.

66
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,400
All of that counts as
damaging Gu Yan's interests.

67
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,680
How do you know all this?

68
00:04:58,222 --> 00:05:00,160
Gu Yan would never
say that about Lin Zhanqiao.

69
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,240
I don't need to know.

70
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:04,960
Can't we just make something up?

71
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,840
Tell me, what company

72
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:08,560
or what editor

73
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:11,400
can really treat an author flawlessly?

74
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,920
If you want to find fault,
isn't that easy?

75
00:05:15,577 --> 00:05:17,320
So, how are you planning
to convince Gu Yan

76
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,760
to accept this kind of negotiation?

77
00:05:18,911 --> 00:05:20,022
No need to convince him.

78
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,280
He doesn't even need to know.

79
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,320
Just tell Gu Yan

80
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:27,160
that we'll negotiate with Lin Zhanqiao.

81
00:05:28,866 --> 00:05:30,000
Once the contract is signed,

82
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,640
we'll announce it right away.

83
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,840
Gu Yan is Sansan.

84
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,640
Then the top two works

85
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,240
on the rankings

86
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,240
will both be written by him alone.

87
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,040
He will

88
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,240
become a legend.

89
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:52,000
A legend on par with Phantom Knight.

90
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:59,460
(Tofato)

91
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,960
Mr. He Han,
I almost didn't recognize you.

92
00:06:19,222 --> 00:06:21,120
If you walked down
the street looking like this,

93
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,360
I wouldn't recognize you.

94
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,400
You just got up?

95
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,280
Going to work?

96
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,688
I've been up for a while.

97
00:06:29,377 --> 00:06:30,488
What did you need?

98
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,640
Well,

99
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,280
I came to tell you

100
00:06:33,822 --> 00:06:35,840
that even though
you've left the literary world,

101
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,320
your legend still lives on.

102
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,480
What are you talking about?

103
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:42,880
You're not here to bring up

104
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,133
that game company buying
the copyright again, are you?

105
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,360
Didn't they offer a sky-high price?

106
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,120
What's the problem?

107
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,080
Offering a sky-high price
is already legendary.

108
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,040
But the real legend is

109
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,160
that we still didn't sell it.

110
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:53,920
Didn't sell it?

111
00:06:54,244 --> 00:06:55,040
What do you mean?

112
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,160
The deal fell through?

113
00:06:56,644 --> 00:06:57,560
I'm telling you again.

114
00:06:57,755 --> 00:07:00,190
It's not that the deal fell through
or that we couldn't sell it.

115
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,320
We're not selling it anymore.

116
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,000
Why not?

117
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,480
Because Ms. Lin said

118
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,040
the core characters and story framework

119
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,960
of Mr. He Han's original novel
must be preserved.

120
00:07:08,977 --> 00:07:10,240
The game company wanted changes.

121
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:11,510
No matter how much money
they offered, we wouldn't sell.

122
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,520
Is she out of her mind?

123
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,630
At a time like this, who cares
about preserving the original novel?

124
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,520
Once a novel's sold,
it's out of your hands.

125
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,377
Saving the company
matters more now, right?

126
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,520
Why care how they change it?

127
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,520
No, I was actually
on Ms. Lin's side back then.

128
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,880
It was quite passionate and moving.

129
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,040
Passionate and moving?

130
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,080
That's just stupid.

131
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:44,020
(Breach of Contract Evidence)

132
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:49,180
(He Han)

133
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,080
I don't believe these seven accusations

134
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,120
came from Gu Yan.

135
00:08:03,022 --> 00:08:05,511
This feels more like
Mr. Fan and Zhao Lanxin's doing.

136
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,320
Why don't we go confirm it with Gu Yan?

137
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:10,480
I will.

138
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,520
But with Chenxing in its current state,

139
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,560
what I need to think about is

140
00:08:17,733 --> 00:08:19,422
what I can use to make him stay.

141
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,600
Get some rest first.

142
00:08:24,755 --> 00:08:27,222
Come back and save the world
after you've recovered.

143
00:08:28,644 --> 00:08:29,844
Then I'll head back first.

144
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:40,500
(Tao Yao: Dream of Wuchuan
Game Development Proposal)

145
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:08,360
Miss,

146
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:09,400
want to go for a ride?

147
00:09:22,822 --> 00:09:23,640
What a coincidence.

148
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,360
Isn't it?

149
00:09:26,222 --> 00:09:27,520
You wouldn't answer my calls,

150
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,720
so I had to come find you.

151
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:30,720
Why are you looking for me?

152
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,866
Didn't you tell me
not to come looking for you?

153
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,120
I came to you

154
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,990
because I wanted you to agree to
the terms offered by the game company.

155
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,680
Get the money first.

156
00:09:40,022 --> 00:09:42,100
I already told them
that I'm not selling it anymore.

157
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,480
So you came to ask me to back you up

158
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,977
because you thought if I showed up,

159
00:09:48,022 --> 00:09:50,133
they wouldn't change
the game's story framework?

160
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,480
Didn't that boss say
he was a fan of your book?

161
00:09:54,111 --> 00:09:57,066
Every other word out of his mouth
was about passion and ideals.

162
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:59,560
So I figured if you showed up,

163
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,440
for your sake at least,

164
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:03,533
there might still be room to negotiate.

165
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,360
Sorry.

166
00:10:06,088 --> 00:10:07,720
I didn't know things were like this.

167
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,440
It's fine.

168
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,240
After seeing him this afternoon,

169
00:10:15,622 --> 00:10:17,040
I realized not selling it to him

170
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:18,120
was the right choice.

171
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,360
Why don't you think it over again?

172
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,800
Whatever he wants to change,
just let him change it.

173
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,940
Honestly, I don't really care.

174
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,040
But I do.

175
00:10:26,644 --> 00:10:28,622
You don't need
to worry about my feelings.

176
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:29,080
Then...

177
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,360
- I don't have any opinion on it.
- You're overthinking this.

178
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:33,440
I didn't consider
your feelings at all this time.

179
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,480
I was thinking about myself.

180
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,200
I've been in this industry for years.

181
00:10:39,355 --> 00:10:41,711
I have standards and principles
I've always held onto.

182
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,440
But this afternoon, I felt

183
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,222
those principles being insulted by him.

184
00:10:45,488 --> 00:10:46,760
That's why I turned him down.

185
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,440
It has nothing to do with you.

186
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,000
Don't feel bad about it.

187
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,640
What about the company?

188
00:11:07,822 --> 00:11:09,222
We'll figure something out.

189
00:11:11,822 --> 00:11:13,240
If it really comes down to it,

190
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,555
there's nothing we can do.

191
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:23,000
Worst case,
I'll do ride-hailing with you.

192
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,760
You can't handle this job.

193
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,240
Why can't I?

194
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,280
I can drive the day shift.

195
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:06,740
(Dida Ride Hailing)

196
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,480
Hello, Dad.

197
00:12:19,377 --> 00:12:21,088
Are you two together right now?

198
00:12:21,355 --> 00:12:22,920
Wait for me. I'm heading over now.

199
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:23,560
What happened?

200
00:12:23,711 --> 00:12:24,280
It's nothing.

201
00:12:24,290 --> 00:12:25,800
If you're going to them,
I'll drive you.

202
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,760
No need. I'll just get a cab.

203
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:27,920
Why waste time getting a cab?

204
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,000
I'll get you there faster.

205
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,000
Send me the address.

206
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,840
My dad said my mom
collapsed from stomach pain.

207
00:12:38,288 --> 00:12:40,160
The ambulance
already took her to emergency.

208
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,920
That serious? Then
why didn't you say so earlier?

209
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,444
Still acting all calm and independent,
like you don't need anyone.

210
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:48,666
I was worried my dad would see
that you're driving ride hailing now.

211
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,540
If he finds out
you stopped writing novels

212
00:12:50,555 --> 00:12:53,066
and started driving instead,
he'll ask a million questions.

213
00:12:53,177 --> 00:12:54,688
I just didn't want to trouble you.

214
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:57,360
As long as your mom's okay,

215
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,600
nothing else matters.

216
00:13:06,755 --> 00:13:08,800
Just drop me off
at the hospital entrance later.

217
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,160
Don't come upstairs.

218
00:13:10,644 --> 00:13:12,977
I'll tell my dad
you had something to do and left first.

219
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:26,060
(Emergency)

220
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,720
Call me if anything happens.

221
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:29,000
Got it.

222
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:55,440
Dad,

223
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,280
Mom's still in emergency?

224
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,040
The doctor said

225
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,444
your mom vomited blood this time.

226
00:14:06,066 --> 00:14:07,920
They suspect there's
a growth in her stomach.

227
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,560
And it doesn't

228
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,360
look good.

229
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:35,260
(Emergency)

230
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,240
Hey, are you going?

231
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,400
No, no.

232
00:15:06,180 --> 00:15:12,940
(Emergency Resuscitation Room)

233
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:32,140
(Emergency Resuscitation Room)

234
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:06,360
Family of Xu Mei.

235
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,000
The doctor said

236
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,160
your mom won't wake up
for another half hour.

237
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:05,440
I'll get going first.

238
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:10,200
At a time like this,

239
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,440
can't you at least wait
until she wakes up,

240
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,840
so she can see you

241
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,600
and talk to you for a bit?

242
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:20,000
If your mom wakes up

243
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,120
and sees I'm still here,

244
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:21,960
chatting with her,

245
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,040
won't she realize

246
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,311
it's not just some minor illness?

247
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:29,960
Call me if anything comes up.

248
00:17:30,333 --> 00:17:31,466
Thanks for everything.

249
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:05,480
Hello?

250
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,160
Hello?

251
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,040
How's your mom doing now?

252
00:18:08,155 --> 00:18:09,355
What did the doctor say?

253
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,400
Maybe

254
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:12,840
she'll need chemotherapy.

255
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,160
She's still asleep right now.

256
00:18:16,977 --> 00:18:18,711
The anesthesia hasn't worn off yet.

257
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:21,040
I don't even know

258
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,680
how to tell her about this.

259
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,688
And I don't know
how to comfort her either.

260
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,960
My dad already went home.

261
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:33,240
I originally thought

262
00:18:33,466 --> 00:18:36,333
that at least at a time like this,
he'd stay and keep her company.

263
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:38,560
But he still left.

264
00:18:40,577 --> 00:18:42,377
Zhangzhu and I aren't asleep yet.

265
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:44,488
We'll come keep you company.

266
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,760
No, it's okay.

267
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:46,480
And you

268
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:49,200
still have work tomorrow morning.

269
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,400
I'll be fine here on my own.

270
00:18:53,111 --> 00:18:54,640
No matter what, I have to face it.

271
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,266
However, it turns out,

272
00:18:57,760 --> 00:18:59,000
I'll get through it somehow.

273
00:19:00,266 --> 00:19:01,266
Alright, then.

274
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:28,440
Still not leaving?

275
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,680
No business anyway.

276
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,244
So I came to keep you company for a bit.

277
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,040
How's your mom?

278
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:43,600
Still asleep.

279
00:19:44,177 --> 00:19:45,733
The anesthesia hasn't worn off yet.

280
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:00,720
Xu Mei.

281
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:02,480
Xu Mei.

282
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:05,000
Xu Mei.

283
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:07,800
Xu Mei, wake up.

284
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,080
Can you hear me?

285
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:11,560
Good.

286
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:16,160
Let me check you over.

287
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:27,040
Raise the head
of the bed a little later.

288
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:28,750
Have her rest
in a semi-reclining position tonight.

289
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:29,080
Okay.

290
00:20:29,090 --> 00:20:30,440
Keep track of the drainage volume.

291
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:31,160
Okay.

292
00:20:40,644 --> 00:20:42,466
Family member,
come with me for a moment.

293
00:20:45,111 --> 00:20:47,822
We'll need to wait for the pathology
results for a confirmed diagnosis.

294
00:20:48,511 --> 00:20:49,360
Our initial assessment

295
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:50,844
is that it looks like lymphoma.

296
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:52,920
The situation isn't very optimistic.

297
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:55,266
She'll most likely
need chemotherapy afterward.

298
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:57,120
You'll need to talk
to the patient gradually

299
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,200
and help her cooperate with treatment.

300
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:15,640
Mom.

301
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:30,480
Mrs. Lin,

302
00:21:30,822 --> 00:21:31,733
we are here now,

303
00:21:31,777 --> 00:21:33,480
so we had Mr. Lin
go home and rest first.

304
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,111
He stayed here the whole time earlier.

305
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,000
I want to go home.

306
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:43,800
Mom,

307
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,480
the doctor said
that after a few days here,

308
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,440
you can go home.

309
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:49,080
It's just that

310
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,400
afterward, you may need

311
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,311
to come back for
treatment a few more times.

312
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,000
What treatment?

313
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:03,360
You said before
that there were a few times

314
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,480
you didn't feel very well.

315
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,400
And before this,

316
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,240
you fainted from bleeding.

317
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:16,520
It was all because
there was a growth in your stomach.

318
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,040
But the doctor said today

319
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,760
they removed it completely.

320
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:24,880
As long as you do a few rounds
of chemotherapy afterward

321
00:22:24,955 --> 00:22:27,200
just to make sure everything
stays under control.

322
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,640
I'm not doing it.

323
00:22:30,311 --> 00:22:32,088
I'm not getting treatment.

324
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:35,200
Just take me home.

325
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,440
It's too much trouble.

326
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:41,680
Getting sick

327
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,080
causes trouble for you

328
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:46,480
and for your father.

329
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,720
Both of you

330
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:52,000
hate trouble the most.

331
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,000
I can't burden you.

332
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:58,440
Mom,

333
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,440
you're sick right now.

334
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,280
Anyone can get sick.

335
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:07,000
And when you're sick,
you need treatment.

336
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:08,800
This isn't a burden.

337
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,720
Exactly, Mrs. Lin.

338
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,000
If we're talking about trouble,

339
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,680
I'm the biggest troublemaker here.

340
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,800
Your daughter can handle someone
as troublesome as me,

341
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,777
so you can leave yourself
to her with peace of mind.

342
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,560
She's busy.

343
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:26,880
If she's busy, I'm not.

344
00:23:26,933 --> 00:23:28,610
When she's busy,
I'll come stay with you.

345
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:29,720
Honestly, Mrs. Lin,

346
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:31,160
I'm a walking headache.

347
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,560
If you don't trouble me a little,

348
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:34,200
I feel uncomfortable instead.

349
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:11,800
We're here.

350
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:13,160
Wake up.

351
00:24:14,066 --> 00:24:15,244
Hurry back and get some sleep.

352
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,200
Thanks.

353
00:24:18,755 --> 00:24:20,600
You should head back
and rest early, too.

354
00:24:22,044 --> 00:24:24,100
What time are you going back
to the hospital today?

355
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:28,440
I'll try to finish up
the company's matters early,

356
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:29,410
and then I'll head over.

357
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:34,040
If anything comes up, call me.

358
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:34,840
Anytime.

359
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:16,080
Ms. Zhao, something came up
at Ms. Lin's home today.

360
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:18,590
If you didn't make
an appointment with her in advance,

361
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,266
she probably won't
be at the office that early.

362
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:21,760
I messaged her before I came.

363
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,350
She only went home
to sleep this morning.

364
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:24,688
She probably hasn't gotten up yet.

365
00:25:26,111 --> 00:25:27,822
Fragile resigned at a time like this?

366
00:25:29,555 --> 00:25:30,533
That's right.

367
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:33,800
I'm here to help Chenxing rise again.

368
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,480
Once your boss gets the news,

369
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:37,100
she won't be able to wait to come over.

370
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,540
I'll go in and wait for her first.

371
00:25:38,911 --> 00:25:40,570
Then, I'll take you to the meeting room.

372
00:25:41,420 --> 00:25:42,155
Morning, Ms. Lin.

373
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:42,800
Morning.

374
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:57,280
Your mother is sick?

375
00:25:58,822 --> 00:26:00,177
What do you want with me?

376
00:26:00,488 --> 00:26:03,088
Judging by your face,
her condition must be pretty serious.

377
00:26:03,422 --> 00:26:05,440
Most people grow old together
with their spouse.

378
00:26:05,644 --> 00:26:06,320
But your father

379
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:08,377
has never really stayed
by your mother's side.

380
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:12,440
Parents everywhere get sick.

381
00:26:12,866 --> 00:26:14,488
And people still get through it.

382
00:26:14,977 --> 00:26:17,000
I don't think I'll be an exception.

383
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:18,800
Deal with problems

384
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,200
as they come.

385
00:26:20,520 --> 00:26:21,480
What a coincidence.

386
00:26:21,866 --> 00:26:23,800
I'm actually here
to help ease your pressure.

387
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:25,040
Pressure isn't a bad thing.

388
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:27,080
I don't need anyone to ease it for me.

389
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:28,360
Especially not you.

390
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,080
Who knows,

391
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,355
you might just become
an even bigger burden?

392
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:33,520
I'll be direct.

393
00:26:34,466 --> 00:26:36,760
I know you're under
huge financial pressure right now.

394
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,120
And the game rights deal for Tao Yao

395
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:39,840
also fell through.

396
00:26:40,244 --> 00:26:42,320
Right now, the only
valuable cards you have left

397
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:44,640
are you and Gu Yan.

398
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:48,360
So you and Gu Yan
should consider joining my company.

399
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,177
Not interested.

400
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:51,480
Externally, you can
still keep your studio name.

401
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,640
Gu Yan will still be your top author.

402
00:26:53,955 --> 00:26:55,480
I'll even sign Hong Qigong over to you.

403
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:57,355
I'm not interested
in becoming your subsidiary.

404
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:02,440
My company's funding also came
from Dingqi Platform.

405
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,600
Didn't you try before

406
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,300
to get investment
from Dingqi Platform too?

407
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:07,640
In the end, it's all the same.

408
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:09,880
Lin Zhanqiao,

409
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,360
money doesn't carry a name.

410
00:27:12,755 --> 00:27:15,044
Money is money.
No matter who gives it to you.

411
00:27:15,377 --> 00:27:16,840
The only thing you need to preserve

412
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,520
is your name.

413
00:27:20,644 --> 00:27:22,933
And I'm willing to
be the one backing that name.

414
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:25,120
You're willing to work for capital.

415
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,040
You want to become part of it.

416
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:30,000
Zhao Lanxin,

417
00:27:30,377 --> 00:27:32,044
you're a person without feelings.

418
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:33,466
Only calculations.

419
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:35,000
No protection.

420
00:27:35,666 --> 00:27:36,520
Only exploitation.

421
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:37,755
What's wrong with that?

422
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:40,080
This industry needs people like you

423
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:41,200
and people like me.

424
00:27:41,622 --> 00:27:43,180
It's precisely because we're different

425
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:45,080
that we should work together.

426
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:46,400
You don't want to work with me.

427
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:48,640
You want to take Gu Yan away.

428
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:53,600
That's right.

429
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,360
But I acknowledge that his success today

430
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:58,520
is partly thanks to you.

431
00:27:59,022 --> 00:28:00,960
And for the sake
of our friendship from school,

432
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:02,960
if I only took Gu Yan away,

433
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:04,880
Chenxing would be finished.

434
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:12,880
Chenxing will continue operating.

435
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:15,840
And my partnership with Gu Yan

436
00:28:17,160 --> 00:28:18,800
will absolutely continue.

437
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:25,440
What if Gu Yan thinks

438
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:26,880
you've held back his career?

439
00:28:27,244 --> 00:28:28,680
Tell him to come to me directly.

440
00:28:28,888 --> 00:28:30,666
How could he
win an argument against you?

441
00:28:31,133 --> 00:28:33,120
Dingqi Platform's lawyers
are talking to him now.

442
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:35,320
Later, they'll speak to you

443
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:36,680
on his behalf.

444
00:29:01,111 --> 00:29:02,800
You don't need to ask me anymore.

445
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:05,000
I won't reveal any details to you.

446
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,400
What you need to do now

447
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:08,600
is go to Lin Zhanqiao

448
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:10,440
and discuss

449
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,160
a mutually beneficial partnership,
instead of

450
00:29:12,333 --> 00:29:14,080
trying to
get information out of me here

451
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,820
so you can stab
Lin Zhanqiao in the back!

452
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,480
Why are you being so impulsive?

453
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:21,640
Zhao Lanxin just called.

454
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:23,840
Of course we want

455
00:29:23,977 --> 00:29:25,888
a mutually beneficial partnership, too.

456
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,440
But...

457
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:30,240
Lin Zhanqiao rejected it.

458
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,200
If you're worried
communication may be difficult,

459
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:35,840
you can entrust us

460
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:37,640
to handle
the follow-up discussions with her.

461
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,920
We will take a professional approach

462
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:42,760
and balance both your interests
as much as possible.

463
00:29:44,977 --> 00:29:47,088
Let me speak to him alone
for a moment, alright?

464
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:02,360
I was your age once, too.

465
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:04,320
I know what you're hesitating over.

466
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:06,360
Love and attachment,

467
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:07,520
right?

468
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:09,600
That's normal.

469
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:11,160
It's human nature, after all.

470
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:16,520
If Lin Zhanqiao's feelings for you

471
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:18,600
are the same as yours for her,

472
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:20,960
and she always puts you first,

473
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:23,800
then I think there's nothing wrong

474
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:24,960
with your choice.

475
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,480
But if

476
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,480
she only sees you as a substitute,

477
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,880
or perhaps not even that,

478
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:36,560
then tell me,
why put yourself through this?

479
00:30:50,311 --> 00:30:51,133
How about this?

480
00:30:51,240 --> 00:30:52,360
Go back and think it over.

481
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:57,400
The questions the lawyers
asked you just now

482
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:59,040
were only routine.

483
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:02,680
I have someone inside Chenxing.

484
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:07,560
So the details
of your dealings with Chenxing

485
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,360
are mostly clear to me.

486
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:13,880
Go back and think carefully.

487
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,480
If you still insist

488
00:31:16,577 --> 00:31:18,111
on sticking with Lin Zhanqiao

489
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:19,640
through thick and thin,

490
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,000
then give me a call.

491
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,280
Everything involving you

492
00:31:24,466 --> 00:31:25,920
that I'm pushing forward here

493
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:27,600
will be stopped completely.

494
00:31:30,480 --> 00:31:31,440
If you stay silent,

495
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,360
then we'll continue.

496
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:39,440
You don't need to say a word.

497
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,280
Ms. Lin,

498
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:58,720
have some water.

499
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,120
Thank you.

500
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:06,000
Zhangzhu told me
you barely slept yesterday.

501
00:32:06,111 --> 00:32:08,111
Why don't you
go back and rest for a while?

502
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:11,600
I do need to head out in a bit.

503
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:13,080
If anything comes up,

504
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:13,960
call me.

505
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:16,080
Also,

506
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:17,760
once Gu Yan updates,

507
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:18,920
send it to me first.

508
00:32:19,400 --> 00:32:19,880
No problem.

509
00:32:20,777 --> 00:32:22,000
Then, I'll get back to work.

510
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:31,240
Ms. Lin.

511
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:35,100
(Keeping stories alive together)

512
00:33:02,822 --> 00:33:04,120
(Doctor's Office)
Alright, thank you.

513
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,360
Thank you. Sorry to trouble you.

514
00:33:05,377 --> 00:33:06,111
It's no trouble.

515
00:33:30,488 --> 00:33:32,888
Want me to lower this
so you can sleep for a while?

516
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:35,880
Excuse me, may I ask

517
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:38,200
when the family of Bed 31 arrived?

518
00:33:38,822 --> 00:33:39,600
Let me check.

519
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,720
He came around 8 AM today.

520
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:43,440
Thank you.

521
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:11,360
Hello?

522
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:13,360
Listen. Just come

523
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:15,000
after you're done with work.

524
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:15,920
No rush at all.

525
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,040
Your mom's doing great.

526
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,840
We're unnecessary now.

527
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:21,320
You're at the hospital now?

528
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:23,320
Your dad, too.

529
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:25,840
Seriously?

530
00:34:25,977 --> 00:34:27,355
You sure you're not mistaken?

531
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:28,760
How could I be mistaken?

532
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,066
The nurse said
he came at eight this morning.

533
00:34:40,010 --> 00:34:41,700
It's like...

534
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:44,750
They have not been together
for a couple of months,

535
00:34:44,750 --> 00:34:46,380
- and it feels kind of...
- Unfamiliar.

536
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:03,160
(This is a scene
I've imagined since I was little.)

537
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,960
(And now, it's finally real.)

538
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,240
(But somehow,)

539
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:14,000
(it feels like it came too late.)

540
00:35:16,466 --> 00:35:18,000
(In a lifetime of several decades,)

541
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,720
(how can love and freedom)

542
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,280
(both exist
without betraying each other?)

543
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:34,480
Thanks.

544
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:38,560
My dad's still upstairs, right?

545
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:39,000
Yeah.

546
00:35:39,080 --> 00:35:40,450
You're not going up there, are you?

547
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,280
Yeah. Why?

548
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:42,080
Don't go up yet.

549
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,240
Let them talk a little longer.

550
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:44,410
Wait until your mom
takes her afternoon nap,

551
00:35:44,422 --> 00:35:45,511
then go find your dad.

552
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,000
Why are you here so early?

553
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,560
Didn't you just get off work?

554
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:53,733
Aren't you going to sleep?

555
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:54,600
I'm not sleepy.

556
00:35:54,900 --> 00:35:56,600
I'll sleep
when I get back this afternoon.

557
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:05,400
What's this?

558
00:36:08,022 --> 00:36:09,333
Don't get mad at me first.

559
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,320
I asked Dai Shan around

560
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:13,080
and found

561
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,120
an authority in this field.

562
00:36:15,133 --> 00:36:16,680
So I printed out your mom's test reports

563
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:18,040
and showed them to him.

564
00:36:18,311 --> 00:36:19,850
Hearing more opinions is always better.

565
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:20,800
Maybe this expert

566
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,080
has a better treatment plan.

567
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,740
You've already helped me
so much these past two days.

568
00:36:30,822 --> 00:36:32,140
I will still be helping tomorrow.

569
00:36:32,444 --> 00:36:33,666
Helping with what tomorrow?

570
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:34,840
Helping your dad move.

571
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:37,720
Move where?

572
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,080
Your dad said he's moving back

573
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,240
to live with your mom.

574
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,120
He told you that?

575
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:48,800
Does my mom know?

576
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:50,200
Not yet.

577
00:36:50,866 --> 00:36:52,840
Your dad said
he'd move his things over first.

578
00:36:52,888 --> 00:36:54,470
After your mom's discharged
the day after tomorrow,

579
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:55,400
he'll tell her himself.

580
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,640
Couldn't my dad have done this earlier?

581
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:20,440
If he'd done it sooner,
would things be better now?

582
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,600
He spent hours

583
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:28,200
talking with my mom today.

584
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,800
I feel like they talked more today

585
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,777
than they had in
all those years combined.

586
00:37:36,066 --> 00:37:37,000
Why are you crying?

587
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,080
This is a good thing.

588
00:38:17,222 --> 00:38:18,080
Have you eaten yet?

589
00:38:20,377 --> 00:38:21,440
I'll go buy you something.

590
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:00,160
Hello?

591
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:02,160
The photo you just sent...

592
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:03,840
Is that your new apartment?

593
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:05,040
Yeah.

594
00:39:05,555 --> 00:39:06,866
According to the contract,

595
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:08,200
I can move in today.

596
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,080
But recently,

597
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,911
the company's been restructuring staff.

598
00:39:11,955 --> 00:39:13,911
I haven't had time
to shop for household stuff.

599
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:16,440
Could you help me
buy some daily necessities?

600
00:39:16,666 --> 00:39:18,688
You mean things like pots and pans?

601
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:22,000
Sure. Then,

602
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,800
after work, I'll go buy some for you.

603
00:39:25,333 --> 00:39:26,720
I'll send them directly to your place.

604
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:27,933
Send me the address later.

605
00:39:58,266 --> 00:39:58,920
What's wrong?

606
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:00,640
I'm heading home early after work.

607
00:40:00,688 --> 00:40:01,760
My mom's coming over.

608
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:02,520
Give this to her.

609
00:40:03,088 --> 00:40:04,800
Tell her the visa's
already been processed.

610
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:05,840
Everything's inside.

611
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:07,311
Where are you going?

612
00:40:07,533 --> 00:40:09,200
If your mom asks, what should I say?

613
00:40:09,377 --> 00:40:10,577
Meeting a client.

614
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:12,040
Alright.

615
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:19,960
Welcome.

616
00:40:27,540 --> 00:40:31,980
(Outpatient Clinic.
Dida Ride Hailing)

617
00:41:12,790 --> 00:41:16,520
♪If I can't have love,
then I'll choose to leave♪

618
00:41:19,750 --> 00:41:23,520
♪Better to part
without winners or losers♪

619
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:27,510
♪In a sea with no one around♪

620
00:41:27,780 --> 00:41:29,280
♪Love sinks into drowning♪

621
00:41:29,490 --> 00:41:31,590
♪Deeply defeated♪

622
00:41:31,770 --> 00:41:33,930
♪I should learn to let go♪

623
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:38,000
♪Leaving no trace behind♪

624
00:41:42,770 --> 00:41:46,780
♪After giving everything,
I couldn't wait any longer♪

625
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:53,690
♪The verdict was already
waiting in the future♪

626
00:41:55,750 --> 00:41:57,530
♪Why bother confessing♪

627
00:41:57,770 --> 00:41:59,360
♪Or thinking about what to say♪

628
00:42:00,622 --> 00:42:02,640
(People who write
countless romantic stories)

629
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:04,480
(may not know)

630
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:07,680
(how to express
love and care in real life)

631
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:12,120
(He Han and I might both
be that kind of person.)

632
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:14,000
♪All the beautiful moments together♪

633
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,000
(Without saying it aloud,)

634
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:16,980
(we cared for the people
the other cared about,)

635
00:42:17,622 --> 00:42:20,177
(expressing the love
the other couldn't put into words.)

636
00:42:21,720 --> 00:42:22,600
(My care for He Wei)

637
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:24,960
(and He Han's care for my parents)

638
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:27,170
(were both like that.)

639
00:42:27,170 --> 00:42:29,760
♪Why be overly generous♪

640
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:33,210
♪Beyond the limits of endurance♪

641
00:42:33,490 --> 00:42:36,750
♪Living in humble silence♪

642
00:42:36,940 --> 00:42:39,920
♪Who is it within the crowd♪

643
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:43,870
♪Gathering strength beneath the waves♪

644
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:50,620
(Outpatient Clinic)

645
00:42:51,150 --> 00:42:54,410
♪Saving the love you once gave me♪

646
00:42:57,340 --> 00:43:04,700
(Thank you.)

647
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

648
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

649
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

650
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

651
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

652
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

653
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

654
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

655
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

656
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

657
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

658
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

659
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

660
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

661
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

662
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

663
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

664
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

665
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

666
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

667
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

668
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

669
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

670
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

671
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

672
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

673
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

674
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

675
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

676
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

677
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

678
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

679
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

680
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

681
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

682
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

683
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
